---
layout: layouts/base.njk
order: 3.5
title: Configure Your Sovereign AI Build
description: An interactive configurator — pick your model, size, quantization, languages, data handling, deployment and compliance, and get a one-page build spec. We explain every choice. Nothing leaves your browser until you send it.
faq:
  - q: Does anything leave my browser while I configure?
    a: "No. Every answer stays in your browser as you go — nothing is sent anywhere until you press Send to sysf.io, which opens your own email client with the spec pre-filled. It's the same principle as everything we build: the model comes to your data — your data never comes to us."
  - q: Can I really choose the model?
    a: "This configurator scopes the starting point. Apertus is our default — Switzerland's fully open LLM. But in a real engagement the evaluation decides: we test open-weight models on a set built from your documents and ship whichever wins. Apertus, Llama or Mistral — the evaluation decides, not the logo."
  - q: Is the build spec a quote?
    a: "No — it's a structured brief, not a quote. It gives us enough to come back with a fixed-scope proposal after a short call. Why we don't publish fixed prices is answered on the <a class='link-underline' href='/pricing/'>pricing page</a>."
  - q: Where do the numbers in the calculators come from?
    a: "The memory figures are plain arithmetic — parameters × bits per weight — using the same numbers as our quantization explainer. The accuracy floors are measured results from our public FINMA benchmark, with the harness open-sourced. Nothing in this page is a projection."
---
